<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Salina on 03-22-2001 10:55 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I have to toss in a few things here.

For 56 levels now, I've relied on a.) my wits b.) my friends.

I corner the market in sheer amounts of invis potions.   ;)  I have jboots, so that helps a great deal.

I generally only get ports to places because I need to get somewhere in a hurry.

I don't charge for rez - I don't have 8 tink's bags in my inventory.

It would be great if we got invis and mana regen and whatever else.

We don't - we most likely never will.  Although it's fun to dream about it, it's not going to happen.  VI has made it brutally clear that we're "balanced" and need no improvements.

This game is about grouping - so if I need a port, I ask a friend.  If that friend needs a rez sometime, you can bet your eboots I'll be there.

Buy potions - yes, it sucks.  No, the other two primary priest classes don't have to.  But paladins, warriors, SKs, rogues, etc. have to buy them.  Deal with it.  Get some charisma gear so you're not losing everything for the purchase.

I generally keep around 6 invis potions on me, plus an EB potion.  I keep a 10 dose sow potion in the bank for naked CR.

Instead of feeling put-upon, ask that shaman you just rezzed for a 10-dose sow potion, or for a future discount.

Ask the druid you just rezzed if they can port you somewhere later.  Same for the wizard.

Believe me, my husband is an enchanter.  If he could have my AC he'd sell his liver.  But he's a caster - they don't get AC.  If I could have clarity 2, I'd sell my liver.   ;)

------------------
Salina Grey
Erudite Templar of Pain, Bertoxxulous
Guild Leader, Glory's Path</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
